  "notes": "Primary data from the official RFEG club page (federative code MM30), which lists per-hole par, hcp (stroke index) and meters for Blancas (M), Amarillas (M) and Rojas (M/F). Cross-checked with Golfshake, whose tee summary matches exactly after yard conversion: White 74/130 at 7,079 yd = 6,473 m; Yellow 71/125 at 6,509 yd = 5,952 m; Red 71/124 at 5,374 yd = 4,914 m. Internal consistency verified: pars sum to 72 (out 37 / in 35), stroke indexes are a permutation of 1-18, and each tee's distances sum exactly to its stated total. RFEG shows Blancas rating as \"74\" (recorded here as 74.0). Note: the course is a full-length par-72 Jack Nicklaus desert/links design, NOT a par-3 layout (that description likely confuses it with the neighboring La Torre Golf Resort short course). One discrepant source, golfingholiday.com, publishes a scorecard with different pars and 6,498 m total that does not match RFEG, the club operator (UGOLF/formerly GNK), or Golfshake; it appears to be mislabeled data from another course and was disregarded. Stroke index allocation is the single set published by RFEG (identical across tees)."
